      <abstract>
        <p>3-Alkyl-thiazolo[3,2-a]benzimidazole derivatives are obtained in high yields via the corresponding 4-alkyl-<italic>N</italic>-3-(2-aminophenyl)-thiazoline-2-thiones which are easily prepared from 1,2-diaminobenzene, CS<sub>2 </sub>and halogenoketones. This new route compares advantageously with the classical mercaptobenzimidazole routes in term of simplicity, isolated yields and availability of the starting materials.</p>
      </abstract>
